    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1180"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1180">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hoshí</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Japan</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 38.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 15th instant, suggesting that, in view of avoiding all risk of
                    error or mischance, due regard should be paid to the usual naval observances by
                    neutral men-of-war which may wish to enter or to depart from any blockaded port
                    in Cuba and in Porto Rico, as well as any other ports that are now or may
                    hereafter be blockaded by the United States during the war with Spain.</p>
                <p>In reply I beg to state that I have taken due note of the contents of your
                    communication, and will not fail to notify the authorities concerned.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Toru Hoshí.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
